OL,3,CNew right to ask for flexible working
OL,4,Cfrom first day in job comes into force
OL,6,FJoeli Brearley, chief executive of the
OL,7,Fgroup, said: "Mothers are more likely
OL,8,Fto shoulder the lion's share of the
OL,9,Funpaid labour required to care for
OL,10,Fchildren and manage a household. As a
OL,11,Fresult, they are more likely to need
OL,12,Fflexible working. Just three in 10 job
OL,13,Fadverts offer flexibility, limiting
OL,14,Fthe progression opportunities and
OL,15,Fearning potential of mothers.
OL,17,F"Then we wonder why the gender pay gap
OL,18,Fwidens when couples have children and
OL,19,Fcontinues to widen further over the
OL,20,Fsubsequent decades."
